; PolyField Start List Script
; Sends athlete start list entries to PolyField via UDP when an event is loaded in FinishLynx.
;
; FinishLynx Scoreboard Configuration:
;   Script:        polyfield-startlist.lss
;   Port:          Network (UDP)
;   IP Address:    <PolyField machine IP>  (use 255.255.255.255 to broadcast on LAN)
;   Port Number:   5002
;   Running Time:  Off
;   Results:       Off
;
; Packet format:  startlist|<eventName>|<lane>|<bib>|<firstName>|<lastName>|<affiliation>
;   One packet is sent per athlete when the start list is loaded.
;   Lane will be empty if no lane assignments are set.
;
; Notes:
;   - Requires the NCP (Network COM Port) plugin (bundled free since FinishLynx 13.00)
;   - Uses port 5002 (separate from the running clock on port 5001)
;   - PolyField firewall must allow inbound UDP on port 5002

;;StartList
\11\01startlist|%e|%l|%i|%f|%s|%a
